2278, "(fr)Welcome to module TSM-103a, pilot. Don't touch the controls until you are told to do so. You will fail this session if you do not follow instructions carefully."

2279, "(fr)This simulation will cover dogfighting techniques. You'll be required to use many of the skills you learned in the preceding modules, such as targeting, matching speed, and primary and secondary weapons control."

2280, "(fr)Begin by targeting my fighter.  You can either use your basic targeting control [Press $t$] or your friendly targeting control. [Press $f$]"

2281, "(fr)You'll notice as I move, a circular indicator moves in front of my ship.  That is the lead indicator.  It shows you where you need to fire your primary weapon to hit your target."

2282, "(fr)Now target the drone. You can use your basic targeting control [Press $t$] or your hostile targeting control. [Press $h$]"

2283, "(fr)The target box in the lower left-hand corner of the HUD displays the distance to and hull integrity of your target."

2284, "(fr)Your target's hull strength is also shown in the lower part of your reticle."

2285, "(fr)As I shoot the drone, watch its hull integrity drop slowly."

2286, "(fr)A good dogfighting tactic is matching speeds with your target.  I want you to match speeds with the drone.  [Press $M$]"

2287, "(fr)Good. Your throttle can be set to automatically match the speed of your target, even as your targets change. Use your auto matching control to toggle this feature on or off. [Press $alt-m$]"

2288, "(fr)Good. You should be on the move at all times during a dogfight."

2289, "(fr)Now destroy the drone."

2290, "(fr)Don't forget you also have missiles.  [Press $spacebar$]"

2291, "(fr)Two new unarmed drones have arrived.  Destroy both of them.  Remember to match their speed.  [Press $m$]"

2292, "(fr)An easy way to target new hostiles is by using auto targeting.  [Press $alt-h$]  This will automatically target your nearest hostile after your current target has either left the area or has been destroyed."

2293, "(fr)This drone is armed.  It will start firing upon you in 10 seconds.  Destroy it."

2294, "(fr)You're sustaining a lot of damage from that drone. You may need to review the first two training modules."

2295, "(fr)Let's try this exercise again.  Here come two more unarmed drones.  Destroy them."

2296, "(fr)Here is an armed drone.  You have 10 seconds before it opens fire.  Destroy it."

2297, "(fr)Pilot, you are by no means ready for combat.  Engage your jump drive to end this simulation.  [Press $alt-j$]"

2298, "(fr)Now comes the fun part.  Five pairs of armed drones will jump in.  Destroy as many as you can."

2299, "(fr)Looks like you've had enough.  Engage your jump drive to end this simulation.  [Press $alt-j$]"

2300, "(fr)You did not follow instructions, pilot. You have failed this training simulation. Engage your jump drive.  [Press $alt-j$]"

2301, "(fr)Great job, pilot.  You have successfully qualified on the Myrmidon space superiority fighter.  Engage your subspace drive.  [Press $alt-j$]"

