Pilots, I have grave news. 6 hours ago, an $h NTF destroyer exited subspace near the $f Patterson $f Installation. Our forces were caught unaware, and a massacre ensued. The hostile destroyer was eliminated, at the loss of the $f GTI $f Patterson, the $f GVC $f Miracle, the $f GTCv $f Retriever, and over 30 $f GTVA fighters and bombers."

3854, "(fr)$b <continued>

In better news, Command has finally made the decision I'm sure you want to hear. I quote:

'The $h Neo-Terran $h Front has gone one step too far this time. Over twenty thousand people were serving aboard the $f Patterson $f Installation alone. It is time the $f GTVA stands up to $h Admiral $h Bosch, and delivers a few heavy blows of it's own!'"

3855, "(fr)$b <continued>

In light of this announcement, we are at last taking action. The $f GTD $f Voyager is set to launch a heavy assault on an $h NTF base in Polaris. The $f 347th $f GBH $f Squad will lead this assault.

Report to mission briefing in ten minutes, pilots. We're nearly in position. 

$b Dismissed."

3856, "(fr)As you have been informed, we are preparing to mount an assault on a nearby $h NTF base of operations. The $f Voyager and the $f 347th will lead this attack. We have already taken up position in Polaris, and are preparing to jump to the location of the base.

Note that there are no Vasudans involved in this assault. Command has made this decision because the relations between us and them are strained enough right now, thanks again to the NTF. We are hoping that this operation will go a long way to resolving this."

3857, "(fr)The $h NTF base consists of the $h NTI $h Lexington, the $h NTM $h Ketracel, five $h Mjolnir class $h Sentry $h Guns (Remote Beam Cannons), and a large complement of fighters and bombers. Quite deadly."

