3954, "(fr)Fifth in the Welcome to the Boonies Series. The Capellan governor arrives in Altair to a surprise kidnap attempt by some well armed pirates. "

3955, "(fr)$b Personal $b Log: Governor Raymond Francis M'kembe
$b Date: November 13, 2372

It has been just over five years since the largest exodus humanity has ever seen. Towards the end of the $r Neo-Terran $r Front rebellion, an ancient portal was discovered in the $g Gamma $g Draconis system. It had been activated by the $r NTF, opening the doorway to another confrontation with the $r Shivans. 

In our arrogance, we thought we had learned from our experience thirty-two years ago."

3956, "(fr)The prophets cried out, warning us of doom on the horizon. We ignored them, believing the lie that we had made for ourselves. The lesson, like the universe, was harsh, and we had forgotten it. We forgot that we had paid the price with our homeworlds. We were cut off from $g Sol and $g Earth, $g Vasuda $g Prime had been laid waste. Scattered across many systems, our colonies became our havens, because we had little choice. Terran, Vasudan, we walk amongst the cold space between the stars as exiles, looking for a place where we might find comfort, solace, and most of all home."

3957, "(fr)We learned the lesson again with $g Capella, a place I once called home. When the Shivans came again, we fled our homes with a hope that we could soon return. We hoped that the GTVA would stop them. Yet after a short-lived victory, we saw our place in the universe. The Shivans tore through our defenses as if they were paper, batting us aside as if we were nothing but a minor annoyance. In efforts to save the rest of our colonies, the jump nodes were collapsed, and the Shivan advance stopped at $g Capella. 

Yet I am left to wonder. I look at the starfield from here at $g Altair, the glow of the star I was born under. We are exiles once again."

3958, "(fr)In all, there were some two hundred million of us cast out of Eden to walk amongst the stars. We look for a place to call home. Many resent us, because the strain on the GTVA economy has thrown us into a new depression. The Vasudans have been kind, showing us a hospitality that we never expected. The wounds of the $b Terran-Vasudan $b War still run deep, it has been heartening to discover their honor and their trust. Yet perhaps they have more in common than we once thought, for they too are exiles, having a deeper understanding of what it is to never return home. 

R. F. M'kembe
Governor of Capella (in Exile)
$b End $b of $b log..."

3959, "(fr)It has been one week since the jump corridor between $g Tau $g Sigma and the $g Altair system was quarantined under provisions from the Beta-Aquilae Securities Act. Any discussion on this matter is $r classified. Travel in this subspace corridor is strictly prohibited, even to $f GTVA personnel. As such, all members of the $g 212th $g Silver $g Scythes present in $g Altair have been temporarily assigned to the Vasudan Installation, $g GVI $g Luxor."

3960, "(fr)The $g GVI $g Luxor is a decommissioned Vasudan $g Typhon class destroyer combined with a $g Ganymede docking ring. It serves its purposes well and is a very flexible design. 

While the $g Luxor's fighter complement can be that of a fully operational destroyer, they are operating at approximately half-strength. Since your stay in $g Altair is for an unspecified time, your skills will be put to use. While assigned to $g Luxor Station, you will be assigned to fly patrols and escort duty alongside your Vasudan colleagues."

3961, "(fr)In spite of the closure of the jump corridor, $g Capellan refugees have begun to arrive in the $g Altair system. In all, some one million refugees are expected to pass through here in the coming weeks. 

Leading the way is the $g GTM $g Alexis, a medical frigate carrying $b Governor R.F. M'Kembe. "

3962, "(fr)As soon as the Alexis arrives, the Governor will be making his way to the $g Luxor to meet with the local Vasudan Commander and a delegation from $b Morgan $b Technologies, who have sponsored the bid of the $g Capellan refugees for a new home in the $g Tau $g Sigma cluster. 

$g Alpha Wing, you are charged with ensuring security in the area. You are responsible for not only the Governor's safety, but for the $g GTM $g Alexis and the rest of the refugee fleet. "

3963, "(fr)$g Delta Wing is flying patrol around $g Luxor Station. They are under your command if you need assistance with the convoy. The $g GVCv $g Qualmotep is also on active duty near the station. 

In an emergency, $g Beta Wing is also on standby as the refugee fleet approaches. They will only be launched at the discretion of $g Luxor station. "

3964, "(fr)We do not know what potential security threats exist. However, there are several pirate groups in operation in these outer systems. They have been plaguing $g GTVA security forces significantly over the past few months. $b Morgan $b Technologies is one of many voices claiming that the $g GTVA does not have the ability to maintain security in this region. 

Keep an eye out for anything out of the ordinary. With the Governor's arrival, it is very possible that one of these pirate groups may attempt some kind of raid. Good luck pilot!"

3965, "(fr)If any security threat was perceived before, now it has become critical. Pirates operating with fighters, bombers and even a small cruiser is one thing, yet for this group to be this well armed indicates something much deeper and dangerous."

3966, "(fr)It seems that Kappa wing had access to GTVA clearance codes in the system. This is a serious breach of security. Their iff appeared as friendly so that they could approach the convoy unmolested. Fortunately, with you and Alpha 2 flying escort, you were able to pick up on the situation before they could carry out their orders."

3967, "(fr)Additionally, the docking bays of the GVI Luxor were sabotaged by a substantial explosion. In so doing, the Governor's Shuttle was stranded outside the station during the firefight, leaving it vulnerable to a kidnap attempt."

3968, "(fr)Governor M'kembe was kidnapped by an Elysium class cargo transport that appeared while all of our fighter wings were tied down in battle. We had warning, pilot, you could have prevented this."

3969, "(fr)As soon as you receive word that the Sneak has arrived, disengage from the main battle and rescue the governor. You will need your afterburners, missiles, and guns."

3970, "(fr)Governor M'kembe's shuttle was damaged and subsequently destroyed from the shockwave of the exploding Sneak. You exercised poor discretion pilot,  a kidnapped governor is better than a dead governor. 

You, on the other hand will be facing disciplinary action for reckless conduct in combat. "

3971, "(fr)Once the Sneak gets too close to the Capellan Shuttle, destroying it will destroy the Governor's craft. You will have to move quickly once the Sneak arrives to destroy it a good distance away from its intended prey. "

3972, "(fr)Congratulations Pilot, you managed to thwart an attempt to kidnap Governor M'kembe. Your quick action and adequate response has prevented what could have been a serious incident. "

3973, "(fr)The death of Governor M'kembe is unacceptable.  His leadership will be sorely missed. We expected better from you, pilot. Your poor conduct has not only seen the death of a well respected leader, but has endangered the secure future of millions of lives. "

3974, "(fr)The GVCv Qualmotep was destroyed in the firefight. Her loss is a substantial blow to security in the area. "

3975, "(fr)The bombers pose a serious initial threat to the Qualmotep, as does the Ithaca. Try to take out the bombers quickly, as well as the Ithaca beam cannons."

3976, "(fr)The Ithaca Deimos-class corvette represents a substantial security threat in the area. While it was driven off, we are going to have to take some steps to track it down. "

3977, "(fr)We were fortunate that the GTFf Cypher was in the area, and helped drive off this pirate attack. However, details of their presence in the system is classified. You are not to discuss this matter, even amongst your wingmates. "

3978, "(fr)Unfortunately, the food convoy fell under attack on the way to their station. The loss of this part of the convoy is serious enough that we will have to look at alternative means of feeding the Capellan Refugees."

3979, "(fr)The GTM Alexis was destroyed enroute to Luxor Station. We are more than disappointed pilot. Over 3,000 lives were lost when she went up. This will be reflected on your permanent record. "

3980, "(fr)The GTM Alexis successfully made it to her rendezvous point. As flagship of the Capellan flotilla, she will hold position at Luxor Station to supervise the operation. Hopefully, the quarantine of the jump node will be short lived, and the Capellans will be able to establish a new home. "

3981, "(fr)Regardless, the situation has now become serious enough that the GTVA is mobilizing its fleets to deal with the security threats in this region. We are going to have our hands full over the next few weeks, pilot."

3982, "(fr)Return to your quarters and give yourself some down time. You are dismissed."

