4118, "(fr)The GTVI and SOC have set up a trap for the rogue Shivan warships that escaped from Vega just before Capella went supernova. Ships and weapons are in short supply, so we must take every advantage we can. Sadly, your choice of loadout is severely limited. We have only managed to scrounge up some Taurets and Myrmidons. I hope you've had some experience with Vasudan fighters."

4119, "(fr)The GVD Kortan has on board a new class of weapon which generates an unusual subspace pulse for 10,000 clicks around. This has two uses. Firstly, it blows the reactors of any small Shivan ships caught in the pulse's inner radius. Secondly, it acts as a lure. For unknown reasons, this type of pulse seems to attract Shivan warships to its source. Scientists hypothesize that it may act as a fake distress signal, but the Shivans aren't usually that compassionate. Whatever it does to the Shivans, we just know it works.

Be careful, Alpha. The Kortan contains the only prototype of the weapon in existence. If it is destoyed, years of research will be lost."

4120, "(fr)We have set up a defense grid consisting of several Mjolnir sentry guns, hidden from the enemy by AWACS. When the Kortan initiates the subspace pulse, another ship, the GVA Galadriel, will divert the path of incoming warships into our trap using a powerful artificial graviton beam. This actually diverts the path of incoming ships through subspace disruptions. The Galadriel will also be hidden from the enemy.

The Kortan can help take down the larger destroyers when it is in place."

4121, "(fr)Special Operations Command, in association with Galactic Terran-Vasudan Intelligence, has set up a trap for Shivan warships who escaped from the recent battle at Vega. This will make the upcoming cleanup operation much easier and save many lives."

4122, "(fr)We have set up an impenetrable line of defense consisting of several Mjolnir sentry guns. They will be invisible to enemy sensors due to high-level AWACS coverage. They should be safe from the Shivans. After all, what you can't hit what you can't see."

